# OSPF Multi-Router Network

## Topology
PC0 → Router3 → Router4 → PC1

## IP Plan
PC0: 192.168.1.10 /24  GW: 192.168.1.1
R3 Fa0/0: 192.168.1.1
R3 Fa0/1: 10.0.0.1

R4 Fa0/0: 10.0.0.2
R4 Fa0/1: 192.168.2.1
PC1: 192.168.2.10 /24  GW: 192.168.2.1

## OSPF Configuration
OSPF Area 0 is used on both routers.

## Verification
- OSPF neighbors formed successfully
- Routes learned dynamically
- Ping between PC0 and PC1 successful

## Troubleshooting
Issue: Initial ping failed  
Cause: ARP resolution  
Fix: Retry ping  
Result: Successful communication
